The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 April is 41,519 (4,805.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 April, there were 112 new confirmed cases (13.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 March, there were 203 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 45% (91 fewer cases).
